(6913, 2, '2014-06-23 21:06:21', '2014-06-23 21:06:21', '[caption id=\"attachment_6915\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://vermontbioenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/report-cover.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-6915\" src=\"http://vermontbioenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/report-cover-300x178.jpg\" alt=\"Vermont releases a report on jobs and growth in the renewable energy industry. \" width=\"300\" height=\"178\" /></a> Vermont releases a report on jobs and growth in the renewable energy industry.[/caption]\r\n\r\nRepresentatives of the clean energy industry celebrated today as the results of several studies and polls corroborated Vermont‚Äôs support for a clean energy future and leadership role in the clean energy industry. Governor Shumlin released the results of <a href=\"http://publicservice.vermont.gov/sites/psd/files/Announcements/Vermont%20Clean%20Energy%20Industry%20Report%20FINAL.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">the first Vermont Clean Energy Industry Report</a>. The report showed that more than 15,000 Vermonters work in the clean energy industry, which expects to see an additional 12% in growth over the next year.\r\n\r\n‚ÄúThe statistics are very encouraging,‚Äù says Gabrielle Stebbins, Executive Director of <a href=\"http://www.revermont.org/main/\" target=\"_blank\">Renewable Energy Vermont</a>, the state trade association for renewable energy businesses. ‚ÄúClean energy businesses are strong and growing. Meanwhile, two independent polls show that 86% of Vermonter‚Äôs support the state‚Äôs goal of getting 90% of its energy from renewable sources by 2050, while 90% believe that making this transition is necessary and important. From every corner of the state, Vermonters are sending a strong message to officials and elected leaders that they want a sustainable energy future. Our officials are responding, and the businesses are too.‚Äù\r\n\r\nSolar electric, modern wood heating, efficiency leaders and others met at Blodgett‚Äôs Supply in the state capital to celebrate job growth, Vermonters saving energy and keeping dollars local. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs been clear to those in the market that Vermont‚Äôs clean energy sector is growing‚Äù, said Chair of the Renewable Energy Vermont Board, Tom Hughes of Sunward Solar. ‚ÄúThe Vermont Clean Energy Industry Report, however, provides verifiable statistics to show that Vermont‚Äôs recent placement as #1 in solar jobs per capita, #2 in solar hot water systems installed, and the lead in farm methane systems is not just anecdotal ‚Äì it‚Äôs real.‚Äù\r\n\r\nThe Report shows that, of the new employment opportunities in the last year, over 81% were new jobs, with the remainder representing new positions for existing employees. It also showed the merging of various business sectors ‚Äì electricians entering the solar electric market and fuel oil dealers offering their customers more efficient heating systems such as air source heat pumps. ‚ÄúThe Clean Energy Industry is not a fringe component of our economy,‚Äù Stebbins said. ‚ÄúAs more Vermonters move towards an efficient and renewable energy future, more businesses are joining the sector as opportunities continue to grow.‚Äù\r\n\r\nMore Vermonters are moving towards a clean energy future, as the jobs results show. Similarly, two polls have been completed this June, showing Vermonters views towards clean energy. The Energy Action Network poll, released today, shows that Vermonters want clean energy, and they want it now: 74% of those polled agreed that transitioning away from traditional fuels needs to happen as quickly as possible. The Vermont Public Interest Research Group poll showed that support for a clean economy crossed party lines, with 93% of self-identified Democrats, 69% of Independents and 49% of Republicans saying they would view clean energy political candidates more favorably than others.\r\n\r\nThe Vermont Clean Energy Industry Report will be repeated over the next two years, with other ongoing polls continuing also.', 'Jobs and Clean Energy', 'Governor Shumlin released the results of the first Vermont Clean Energy Industry Report showing that more than 15,000 Vermonters work in the clean energy industry, which expects to see an additional 12% in growth over the next year.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jobs-clean-energy', '', '', '2015-01-12 15:57:18', '2015-01-12 20:57:18', '', 0, 'http://vermontbioenergy.com/?p=6913', 0, 'post', '', 0),
