(7475, 1, '2015-10-19 06:36:10', '2015-10-19 10:36:10', '<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://www.meachcovefarms.org/images/890_Field_to_Flue_Open_House_poster.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"889\" height=\"1151\" />\r\n\r\nVermont-grown grasses are being used to heat the Biomass Building ‚Äì a 4,200 square foot commercial building at Meach Cove Farms in Shelburne. Local residents, community leaders, and renewable energy enthusiasts are invited to visit Meach Cove Farms Friday, October 23 ‚Äì Saturday, October 24 for an Open House to learn how grass pellets are generating heat in a biomass boiler ‚Äì an emerging source of bioenergy in Vermont.\r\n\r\nMeach Cove Farms is a 1,000-acre certified organic farm primarily growing soy beans, wheat, rye, and corn as well as wine grapes, woodlands, and switchgrass trial plots for use in grass energy production. The Open House will offer a complete demonstration of the Grass Pellet Heating Equipment Combustion Optimization project ‚Äì the first project in New England to showcase grass test plots, densification equipment, and an EvoWorld biomass boiler that burns the grass.\r\n\r\nMeach Cove Farms began collaborating with Dr. Sidney Bosworth of the University of Vermont College of Agriculture and Life Sciences and the <a href=\"http://vermontbioenergy.com/about/\" target=\"_blank\">Vermont Bioenergy Initiative</a> in 2009 to assess the potential of different species of grass as solid biofuel for heating applications.\r\n\r\nIn September 2011 Meach Cove Farms was awarded an USDA Natural Resources Conservation Service Conservation Innovation Grant to research the feasibility of Vermont grown grass pellets and heating equipment potential as an emerging renewable energy source in Vermont. The biomass boiler being featured at the Open House was funded through a Conservation Innovation Grant (CIG) administered by the Natural Resources Conservation Services.\r\n\r\nIF YOU GO:\r\n\r\nMeach Cove Farms is located at 310 Beach Road in Shelburne (off Bostwick Road, 1.6 miles west of Rte 7). The Open House runs from 9 am ‚Äì 12 noon both Friday and Saturday, October 23-24. There is no cost and both days are open to the public. More info at <a href=\"http://www.meachcovefarms.org\">www.meachcovefarms.org</a>, 802-985-9218.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Field to Flue Open House at Meach Cove Farms', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'field-to-flue-open-house-at-meach-cove-farms', '', '', '2016-12-05 17:07:46', '2016-12-05 22:07:46', '', 0, 'http://vermontbioenergy.com/?p=7475', 0, 'post', '', 0),
